security: harden HTTP transport, address/invoice validation, batch notional cap

- Startup guard: process.exit(1) when authEnabled but MCP_AUTH_TOKEN is unset,
  preventing silent exposure of auth-gated tools on the HTTP server.
- Rate limiting: express-rate-limit middleware (120 req/min per IP, configurable
  via MCP_RATE_LIMIT) applied to POST/GET /mcp before auth middleware.
- Crypto address validation: validateCryptoAddress() added to validation.ts with
  per-currency regex rules (BTC, ETH, USDC, USDT, LTC, BCH, XRP). Called in
  create_withdrawal before any API call; returns INVALID_ADDRESS on failure.
  Tool description updated to warn about irreversibility.
- BOLT-11 invoice validation: lightning_withdrawal now rejects non-BOLT-11 strings
  via prefix regex before the API call (INVALID_INVOICE). Zod min length 1 to 50.
- Dead man's switch HTTP guard: schedule_cancel_all returns TRANSPORT_NOT_SUPPORTED
  on the HTTP transport where restarts silently drop in-memory timers. register()
  now accepts transport: "stdio" or "http" (default "stdio").
- Batch orders notional cap: place_batch_orders accepts optional max_notional;
  rejects the entire batch pre-API-call if sum(amount x limit_price) exceeds cap
  (market orders contribute 0). Returns NOTIONAL_CAP_EXCEEDED.
- 20 new unit tests (136 to 156 total). Updated existing withdrawal tests to use
  real bech32 addresses instead of placeholder string.
- CHANGELOG and README updated with all changes and new env var table.
